Simple php script that install the latest version of wordpress to the current directory.

WHY?
It's a lot easier to use this, then to upload individual wordpress files manually. Also just incase you don't have access to cpanel.

1) checks folder settings
2) downloads the latest wordpress to the temp directory
3) unzips wordpress to current directory
4) moves wordpress from ./wordpress to current directory
5) chmods all files to 755
6) deletes wordpress directory
7) deletes downloaded temp wordpress zip file
8) deletes itself